        <abstract>
            <p>An awful row at the Linnean Society. William Carruthers and Co. packed a meeting to throw out a decision of the Council. He was beaten by one vote (more than two-thirds majority needed).</p> 
<p>Spent two hours with Lyell talking about Thomas Belt’s book [<hi rend="italic">The naturalist in Nicaragua</hi> (1874)]: "the tropical old Glaciers beat the seance I do think".</p> 
            <p>Lyell agrees that the glacial epoch is the great geological crux of the day. Lowering of the ocean level must also be investigated.</p> 
<p>Curious about A. C. Ramsay’s paper coming at Royal Society on 29th ["On the comparative value of certain geological ages", <hi rend="italic">Proc. R. Soc. Lond.</hi> 22 (1874): 145–8].</p>  
<p>Huxley’s new book [? <hi rend="italic">Critiques and addresses</hi> (1873)].</p> 
        </abstract>
